<paragraph id="F311E23DD55D2F011CDDFC7C42E5FC4E" blockId="15.[144,253,930,954]" box="[144,253,930,954]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2144">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD55D2F011CDDFC7C42E5FC4E" box="[144,253,930,954]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2144">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F311E23DD55D2F011CDDFC1541F5FBB6" blockId="15.[144,1104,970,1090]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2144">Pronotum black, with vertical yellow band on anterior margin extended from anterior lobe to dorsum and, another, running along lateral margins above humeral angles to apex of posterior process; in lateral view, fusiform, highly elevated above humeral angles and gradually descending towards apex of posterior process.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F311E23DD55D2F011CDDFBA4432AFB66" blockId="15.[144,306,1146,1170]" box="[144,306,1146,1170]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2144">
