<paragraph id="F311E23DD5422F1E1C99F9DB460BF969" blockId="16.[212,1172,1541,1693]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2145">
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5422F1E1C99F9DB43E4F9E9" authority="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista, 2010" authorityName="Sakakibara &amp; Evangelista" authorityYear="2010" box="[212,508,1541,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="2145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliquifasciata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5422F1E1C99F9DB43E4F9E9" box="[212,508,1541,1565]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2145">Membracis obliquifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="DAE98354D5422F1E1E4BF9DB407AF9E8" box="[518,610,1541,1564]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2145" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName id="34AE99BED5422F1E1F3BF9DB41F1F9E9" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[886,1001,1541,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Membracis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="2145" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foliata">
<emphasis id="C1DA3E2FD5422F1E1F3BF9DB41F1F9E9" box="[886,1001,1541,1565]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2145">M. foliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) in having the frontal yellow band covering the anterior margin of pronotum and the posterior band running along the lateral margins until the apex. It differs, however, in the form of pronotum, being fusiform instead of semicircular and the posterior yellow band somewhat oblique, not curved in a straight angle up to the dorsal margin.
</paragraph>
